A mathematical rate is composed of a numerator, denominator, and time period of 
observation. Deciding who is in the denominator is a key, yet difficult task 
given the blurred boundaries of chronic illness, in examining the quality of 
care for dying patients. We propose two potential solutions. First, one could 
